The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Butt is new PCB chief 
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Butt is new PCB chief 
                      
	Karachi: Former Test player Ijaz Butt was on Tuesday appointed the new chairman of the Pakistan Cricket Board by President Asif Ali Zardari. The Sports Ministry is yet to make it official, but PCB officials have confirmed that they had been told Butt would head the board.         
	[The Telegraph had reported way back in May that Butt is the frontrunner]         
	Butt, who played eight Tests, has been active on the cricket scene for some time now and is presently a member of the PCBs governing body. (PTI)                                                                                                                          
